    72,
    "Gloucestershire Mince Pie",
    "",
    "1 1/2 hours",
    "<p>This is a good dish to have if economising before or after the big event. It is&nbsp;very tasty and a convenient meal to eat whilst sitting watching television.</p>",
    "1 1/2lbs cooked *potatoes* (to slice)\n1 tablespoon *oil*\nSalt and pepper\n1 *onion*, chopped\n2 *carrots*, diced\n2 sticks *celery*, chopped\n2oz frozen *peas*\n1lb lean *minced beef*\n2 tablespoons *sweet chutney*\n1/2 pint *beef stock*\n2 tablespoons *plain flour*\n2 tablespoons *tomato puree*\n3 tablespoons water\n4oz grated Double Gloucester *cheese*\n",
    "Heat oil in pan nd cook onion for about 5 minutes until soft.\nAdd carrot and celery. Cook for 5 minutes.\nAdd mince and cook, stirring until it changes colour. Stir in chutney and stock. Cover and simmer for 30 minutes. Add purée.\nBlend the flour with the water and stir into the mince. Bring back to boil, stirring all the time and then simmer for 5 minutes.\nSeason to taste and then add peas. Turn into a deep ovenproof dish and cover with sliced potatoes. Sprinkle on cheese. Cook for 30 minutes at gas 4 / 350 elec / 180c.\n",
